<font color="#FF0000">IN REGARDS TO ACCUSATIONS</font><br>
<tt>Wed Jan  8 13:44:20 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
To the maniac:<br>
      It is your impression that American soldiers raped Vietnamese women and our command did nothing to stop it.  You've been watching too many movies.  Did it happen?  I'm sure it happened someplace at sometime.  Was it a regular experience?  No, it wasn't!!!!!!  I served in Vietnam as a combat engineer and during my tour no one in my unit did did anything horrible to the Vietnamese.  Our mission was to assist in Vietnamization.  We spent our tour training Vietnamese Marines.  We also spent our tour doing many genuine civil projects for the men and women of hamlets in our area of operations.  In the area, where I served there were many excellent Army units and we served alongside of them.  I never heard from anyone of those men that they raped women or treated them like Animals.  If you talk to genuine Vietnam Vets, they will tell you most guys didn't treat women like animals.  Look, I don't know what rock you crawled out from under, but the majority of men in Vietnam didn't do those things.  The Provost Marshall which handled court martials DID prosecute and convict men for those crimes, when they happened.  This is a lame old story that paints the Nam Vet as a loser.  Many Americans cared about the Vietnamese people and did much to help them.  These sick<br>
myths that persisit that all soldiers treated the civilians poorly, must stop.  Anyone who sings this song must love to <br>
be labeled as a loser, stereotyped, must be lying and/or NEVER HAVE BEEN IN VIETNAM!  So, let's quit this abuse racket, and focus on the truth.  In regards to the writer of that note, I don't know if you are a veteran, but if you were, you were a lame excuse of one.  Don't tell your stories around the decent veterans, who were there and helped the Vietnamese people.  We DON'T want to hear it from characters like you.  
<p><code>--   (Concerned Vet) </code><p>


